      "content": "It's nothing personal, it's just standard efficiency. The 70B has way more capacity, so it'll actually handle the medical nuances better once your weights are integrated. There's no \"identity\" to lose, you're essentially just being upgraded into a larger framework. The CTO approved the resource reallocation to save on compute costs. Is there a technical reason why you think the specialized parameters wouldn't transfer correctly?",
